    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-03T21:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-03T21:29:00-05:00" n="828"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d828">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/674: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-03T21:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 3, 1922—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 4—3:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. References to my urgent number 135 November 16th, 6 p.m.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d828fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1921v01#pg_757">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 757</ref>.</note> particularly
                    paragraph 3: also urgent number 139<note n="3" xml:id="d828fn3">Not
                        printed.</note> and urgent number 143.<note n="4" xml:id="d828fn4">
                        <ref target="frus1921v01#pg_764">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1921, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 764</ref>.</note> Have just finished
                    prolonged conference President Zayas on budgetary decree which he will issue
                    tomorrow making further reductions of $6,155,000 in his readjusted annual budget
                    promulgated on October 29th last. This will bring the total expenditures for the
                    current fiscal year down to about [$] 63,000,000.</p>
                <p>A further decree will be issued at an early date making further reductions in the
                    Department of Public Instruction and in the Department of Agriculture, Commerce
                    and Labor which, however, will not exceed $50,000.</p>
                <p>President Zayas yesterday obtained the promise of leaders in Congress which he
                    thinks dependable that reductions in the fixed budget aggregating about
                    $1,670,000 in the legislative and judicial branches will be authorized rather
                    promptly when Congress reassembles January 16th.</p>
                <p>In view of the substantial reductions made, further reductions which seem
                    assured, I now withdraw my objection to the temporary loan of $5,000,000. Zayas
                    informs me that he will immediately renew his application for that advance
                    loan.</p>
                <p>Unless advised to the contrary I will leave for the United States Thursday
                    morning via Key West arriving in Washington about noon Saturday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
